This project introduces a Smart Energy-Efficient Load Monitoring and Control System built using the ESP32 microcontroller. The system is designed to reduce unwanted power consumption and improve electrical safety in home, educational, and industrial environments.
The ESP32 automatically logs the ON/OFF working duration of connected loads through a built-in Working-Time Tracker. This runtime information is displayed on an LCD screen, helping users monitor energy usage without requiring a mobile app or PC.
For safety, the system integrates a temperature sensor and current sensor to continuously analyze load performance. If overload or overheating is detected, the ESP32 triggers an auto cut-off and alerts the user, helping prevent equipment damage and electrical hazards.
The system is built using low-cost components and supports future expansion such as IoT connectivity, cloud analytics, mobile notifications, and smart automation.
🔑 Key Features
Automatic Energy Saving (auto-off for idle/unsafe loads)
Load Runtime Tracking (ESP32-based logging)
Safety Protection (overload & overheating auto-cutoff)
Real-time Display (current, temperature, runtime)
Low-Cost, Reliable, Expandable Smart Energy System
